comment:
* An Iterator specialized for {@code int} values.
     * @since 1.8

methods.name: int nextInt()
methods.comment:
* Returns the next {@code int} element in the iteration.
         *
         * @return the next {@code int} element in the iteration
         * @throws NoSuchElementException if the iteration has no more elements

methods.name: void forEachRemaining(IntConsumer action)
methods.comment:
* {@inheritDoc} * @implSpec *

The default implementation behaves as if: * 

{@code
         *     while (hasNext())
         *         action.accept(nextInt());
         * }

methods.name: Integer next()
methods.comment:
* {@inheritDoc}
         * @implSpec
         * The default implementation boxes the result of calling
         * {@link #nextInt()}, and returns that boxed result.

methods.name: void forEachRemaining(Consumer<? super Integer> action)
methods.comment:
* {@inheritDoc}
         * @implSpec
         * If the action is an instance of {@code IntConsumer} then it is cast
         * to {@code IntConsumer} and passed to {@link #forEachRemaining};
         * otherwise the action is adapted to an instance of
         * {@code IntConsumer}, by boxing the argument of {@code IntConsumer},
         * and then passed to {@link #forEachRemaining}.
